{"parse":{"title":"Action based learning questions","pageid":47801928,"revid":859486810,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-lead_missing\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Wiki letter w.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/60px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/80px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"44\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>has no <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Lead_section\" title=\"Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Lead section\">lead section</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help by adding an introductory section to this article. For more information, see the <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Layout\" title=\"Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Layout\">layout guide</a>, and Wikipedia's <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Lead_section\" title=\"Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Lead section\">lead section guidelines</a> to ensure the section will be inclusive of all the essential details. Please discuss this issue on the article's <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Talk:Action_based_learning_questions&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Talk:Action based learning questions (page does not exist)\">talk page</a>.</span>  <small><i>(September 2018)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style ambox-Orphan\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"display: none\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Wiki letter w.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/60px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/80px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"44\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>is an <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Orphan\" title=\"Wikipedia:Orphan\">orphan</a>, as no other articles <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere&amp;target=Action_based_learning_questions&amp;namespace=0\">link to it</a></b>. Please <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Link\" title=\"Help:Link\">introduce links</a> to this page from <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3ASearch&amp;redirs=1&amp;search=Action+based+learning+questions&amp;fulltext=Search&amp;ns0=1&amp;title=Special%3ASearch&amp;advanced=1&amp;fulltext=Action+based+learning+questions\">related articles</a></span>; try the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//edwardbetts.com/find_link?q=Action_based_learning_questions\">Find link tool</a> for suggestions.  <small><i>(September 2015)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Action Based Learning Question Types</b>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Overview\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Overview</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Types_of_Questions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Types of Questions</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Closed_Questions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Closed Questions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Open_Questions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Open Questions</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Benefits_in_Education\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Benefits in Education</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Overview\">Overview</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Action_based_learning_questions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Overview\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>One of the keys to effective Action Learning is asking the \"right question\". When asked to the right people at the right time, these questions result in obtaining the necessary information. \nThe Action Learning process, which primarily uses a questioning approach, can be more helpful than offering advice because it assumes that each person has the capacity to find their own answers.\n</p><p>Normally, the purpose of asking a question is to obtain information. However, in Action Learning, the purpose is to help someone else to do one or more of the followinf:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Think more deeply</li>\n<li>Explore new options and <a href=\"/wiki/Point_of_view_(philosophy)\" title=\"Point of view (philosophy)\">perspectives</a></li>\n<li>Reflect in order to make better choices and decisions</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Types_of_Questions\">Types of Questions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Action_based_learning_questions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Types of Questions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Closed_Questions\">Closed Questions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Action_based_learning_questions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Closed Questions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Closed questions involve a technique which does not allow the respondents to develop their response. It can do so by limiting respondents with a strict, limited list of answer choices. Answers are mostly <a href=\"/wiki/Monosyllabic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Monosyllabic\">monosyllabic</a> words or short phrases. For example, some closed questions can only be answered by a \u201cYes\u201d or \u201cNo\u201d.\n</p><p>Closed questions should not be interpreted as simple questions. They can be of varying levels of difficulty, and may make the respondent think before answering. Take this phrase for example: \"When two quantities are dependent on each other, does an increase in one always leads to an increase in the other?\".\n</p><p><i>Usage Of Closed Questions:</i>\n</p>\n<ul><li>To give facts</li>\n<li>To help keep control of the conversation with the questioner</li>\n<li>To open up a conversation</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Open_Questions\">Open Questions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Action_based_learning_questions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Open Questions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Open questions allow the respondent to expand or explore in their response, and do not have a single correct response. This gives the respondent the freedom to discover new ideas, consider different possibilities, and decide on the course of action which is right for them.\n</p><p>Open-ended questions are not always long - they may be short as well as open-ended. Shorter questions often have equal or greater impact than longer ones. When asking shorter questions, it is easier to be perceived as abrupt or even rude. When questioning an Action Learning set, it is important to be aware of one's tone and language. The goal is usually to ask challenging questions, or to challenge the respondent's perspective.\n</p><p><i>Usage Of Open Questions:</i>\n</p>\n<ul><li>To encourage discussion of opinion and feelings.</li>\n<li>To think and reflect</li>\n<li>To give control of the conversation to the <a href=\"/wiki/Respondent\" title=\"Respondent\">respondent</a></li>\n<li>To expand upon a closed question</li>\n<li>To aid in the realization of the depth of a situation</li>\n<li>To help to learn more about an individual</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Benefits_in_Education\">Benefits in Education</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Action_based_learning_questions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Benefits in Education\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>To help students organize their thoughts</li>\n<li>To assist students as they analyze causes and effects</li>\n<li>To provide opportunities for students to use evaluative thinking skills</li>\n<li>To incite students to listen to the ideas of others, synthesize information, and form opinions on the issue at hand</li>\n<li>To aid students' memories</li>\n<li class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></li>\n<li>To direct self <a href=\"/wiki/Feedback\" title=\"Feedback\">feedback</a> for an individual</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Action_based_learning_questions&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n</div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://changingminds.org/techniques/questioning/open_closed_questions.htm\">http://changingminds.org/techniques/questioning/open_closed_questions.htm</a></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation journal\">Schuman, Howard; Presser, Stanley (1979). \"The Open and Closed Question\". <i>American Sociological Review</i>. <b>44</b> (5): 692\u2013712. <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.jstor.org/stable/2094521\">2094521</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Sociological+Review&amp;rft.atitle=The+Open+and+Closed+Question&amp;rft.volume=44&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=692-712&amp;rft.date=1979&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2094521&amp;rft.aulast=Schuman&amp;rft.aufirst=Howard&amp;rft.au=Presser%2C+Stanley&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAction+based+learning+questions\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li>Thalheimer, W. (2003, January). The learning benefits of questions. Retrieved September 12, 2015, from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.worklearning.com/ma/PP_WP003.asp\">http://www.worklearning.com/ma/PP_WP003.asp</a></li>\n<li>Hale, R.I. 2003 How Training Can Add More Value to the Business, part 1, Industrial and Commercial Training, Volume 35, No. 1, pp. 29\u201332.</li>\n<li>Hale, R.I. 2003. How Training Can Add More Value to the Business, part 2, Industrial and Commercial Training, Volume 35, No. 2, pp. 49\u201352.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2172\nCached time: 20180921091103\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: true\nCPU time usage: 0.084 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.127 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 251/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 11153/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 137/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 3/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.041/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.74 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  107.714      1 -total\n 50.59%   54.496      1 Template:Lead_missing\n 40.68%   43.814      2 Template:Ambox\n 30.82%   33.196      1 Template:Cite_journal\n 10.57%   11.389      1 Template:Orphan\n  7.77%    8.367      1 Template:Reflist\n  1.93%    2.084      1 Template:Main_other\n  1.78%    1.919      1 Template:Monthyear-1\n  1.76%    1.894      1 Template:Monthyear\n  1.27%    1.371      2 Template:PAGENAMEU\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:47801928-0!canonical and timestamp 20180921091102 and revision id 859486810\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Wikipedia_introduction_cleanup_from_September_2018"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"All_pages_needing_cleanup"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Pages_missing_lead_section"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Articles_covered_by_WikiProject_Wikify_from_September_2018"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"All_articles_covered_by_WikiProject_Wikify"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Orphaned_articles_from_September_2015"},{"s